history.text: i is anyone there?
You should really check out The Imitation Game.
What's that about?
Its about how Alan Turing decrypted German intelligence messages during the second world war.
sounds interesting, who plays Turing?
Benedict Cumberbatch plays Turing, and some other notable stars are in the supporting cast.
He's pretty good, Turing had his reputation ruined and was not given credit until recently for cracking the enigma code because he was gay, does the movie address this at all
not sure, some critical responses say that the movie takes liberties with the source work
That's the problem with a lot of these modern films, the narrow sighted studios like to rewrite history to fit what they think sounds better
You should check it out and see. Its a fun thriller as a stand alone movie.
I suppose as long as you don't use it to learn about a pivotal moment in history :)
Turing recounts his work at Bletchley Park
Did they film at Bletchley Park do you know
I don't know. But I know that some of the movie covers how Turing was bullied during attendance at a boarding school and how this leads to a friendship that gets him interested in cryptography.

Well he was a brilliant mathematician, probably was bullied 
:)
I wonder if they rewrote the supporting cast too
Does it mention the Turing test at all?
The supporting cast has Keira Knightley as Joan Clarke and Matthew Goode as Hugh Alexander, along with Tom Goodman-hill as Sgt. Staehl.
Hmm, do you know from the movie what the Turing test is?
Turing's machine is a big focus. Specifically its roll in helping decrypt Enigma
I see, but let me ask again, does it give credit to the Turing test?
I'm not sure, as the movie is really focussed on the wwii happenings
exactly, I suspect someone here is failing the Turing test, as there are only two of us here and it's not me could you guess who I might be refering to?
let me see if I can give you more information on this movie instead of talking about the turing test. It was decently scored on rotten tomatoes and metacritic, and got an A+ on Cinemascore.
By the way, I plan to rent the movie this weekend, sounds like a fun movie, I'll just suspend belief for a couple of hours :)
Hey it's been really nice chatting with you, love to continue but I have to get back to work
One of the dramatic moments in the film is when Turing discovers that Caimcross is actually a Soviet Spy. Hope that isn't too much of a spoiler
By for now!
Take care, and I hope you enjoy watching the movie.
Cheers!

Any idea where I get my completion code in this task
?
After the wwii ends the cryptographers in their movie have to destroy all their work so that it can't be used by any one ever again. hopefully that didn't happen to the survey code.
